// Buffalo⁶ set: z_{n+1} = |Re(z^6)| + i|Im(z^6)| + c.
// Mandelbrot analogue — pixel = c, z₀ = 0.
// The degree-6 Buffalo map raises z to the sixth power then folds both real
// and imaginary components through absolute value. At degree 6 the full
// bilateral symmetry produces a 12-fold (2·6) arrangement of lobes around
// the central body with each lobe pair separated by deep cusp valleys.
// The Buffalo fold at degree 6 creates a distinctive "snowflake" boundary
// where each of the 12 outermost cusps hosts miniature self-similar copies.
// Smooth coloring: log₂(6). Supports normal-map shading (colorScheme 50-63).
uniform float uTime;
uniform vec2  uResolution;
uniform vec2  uCenter;
uniform float uZoom;
uniform float uIterations;
uniform float uBailout;
